Primary Key helps to uniqely identify row/data-point/observation
Primary key can also be unique by combining two or more columns together to create a unique value, which is known as COMPOSITE PRIMARY KEY.

CONTROLLED CROSS JOIN
This is the type of join returns more than number of rows that any type of join can return, but less than the maximum number of rows

Using Primary key of a table as an ON condition
When using primary key of a table as an "ON" condition, 
the maximum number of row output is the maximum number of rows available in either of the tables
